The article is outdated. It confuses Judges of the Peace and Promiscuous family judges with ordinary promiscuous judges. This is due to the change in regulation, most notably brought about by the law 1564 of 2012.

There are no summary process for criminal offenses in Colombia. Also promiscuous judges are not the "lowest" category of judges in Colombia. They are equal to normal municipal judges. The "lowest" judges would be "Peace Judges" who are not paid.
